RenderLevelStageEvent
public static class RenderLevelStageEvent.Stage extends Object
A time during level rendering for you to render custom things into the world.

    • AFTER_TRANSLUCENT_BLOCKS

      public static final RenderLevelStageEvent.Stage AFTER_TRANSLUCENT_BLOCKS
      Use this to render custom block-like geometry into the world. Due to how transparency sorting works, this stage may not work properly with translucency. If you intend to render translucency, try using AFTER_TRIPWIRE_BLOCKS or AFTER_PARTICLES. Although this is called within a fabulous graphics target, it does not function properly in many cases.

    • AFTER_TRIPWIRE_BLOCKS

      public static final RenderLevelStageEvent.Stage AFTER_TRIPWIRE_BLOCKS

    • AFTER_PARTICLES

      public static final RenderLevelStageEvent.Stage AFTER_PARTICLES
      Use this to render custom effects into the world, such as custom entity-like objects or special rendering effects. Called within a fabulous graphics target. Happens after entities render.
      Siehe auch:
      • ForgeRenderTypes.TRANSLUCENT_ON_PARTICLES_TARGET

    • AFTER_WEATHER

      public static final RenderLevelStageEvent.Stage AFTER_WEATHER
      Use this to render custom weather effects into the world. Called within a fabulous graphics target.

    • AFTER_LEVEL

      public static final RenderLevelStageEvent.Stage AFTER_LEVEL

      finishes.
